-2110560169.text: "However, since cytoplasmic p27 re-expression only partially rescued apoptosis in p27 knockdown cells, it is likely that both p27 functions (apoptosis suppression in the cytoplasm and CDK2 inhibition in the nucleus) play roles in modulating apoptotic responses to lapatinib treatment Although the mechanisms by which cytoplasmic p27 blocks apoptosis are unknown, this appears to be a widespread feature of cancer cells, and related findings have been reported in mitogen depleted MCF7 breast cancer cells [XREF_BIBR] and in U87-MG glioma cells, that express abundant cytoplasmic p27."
